laboratory_examinations.findings: New bilateral diffuse microcalciﬁcations, with predominance in the left lower inner quadrant; no associated masses or lymphadenopathy.
Numerous bilateral simple fluid-filled cavities, representing cysts and dilated ducts, without discrete solid masses.
Bilateral patchy heterogeneous abnormal enhancement, more prominent in the lower inner and upper outer quadrants of the left breast.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Postprocessing of the time–signal-intensity curves showed slow initial enhancement and continued progressive enhancement over time.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Large, globular, smoothly contoured microcalciﬁcations within benign ducts without evidence of malignancy.
